CAPE TOWN – A police officer shot and killed two people on Thursday morning before turning the gun on himself in a hostage drama in Mitchells Plain, Cape Town. Police and Western Cape emergency officials are on the scene at a home in Begonia Street. “Circumstances surrounding a hostage situation this morning at 09:10 in Begonia Street, Lentegeur are being investigated,” police said in statement. “According to information at hand, a 41-year-old police member who worked at Lentegeur SAPS shot and killed himself. “Two women, 54 and 27-years-old respectively, were also shot and fatally wounded. Inquest cases are under investigation," Western Cape police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana added. eNCA